text.tspan: Index of US maternal mortality and female labor force
The index of maternal mortality (maternal deaths per 100,000 live births) and female labor force participation (% of
the female population that is economically active) is calculated as maternal mortality and FLFP in each year divided
by the starting value in 1900 (therefore 1900 = 100). In 1900, maternal mortality was 850 deaths per 100,000 live
Data source: OWID based on Gapminder and World Bank, OWID based on Olivetti (2013)
